{{Quote|The Star Core, that's what exploded, it was only in the development stage and good thing, too, or this moon would be about half the size it is currently. Fortunately, the reaction was limited to a radius slightly smaller than the city. It's supposed to be a new type of power supply that can run practically an entire planet.... or even worse, another Death Star!|A Rebel officer, to [[Stoer Kilos]]|<ref name="RiR">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=66906&resource=features|text=Ruins of Restuss}}</ref>}}
The '''Star Core''' was a small object small enough to fit into a [[Backpack/Legends|backpack]] yet powerful enough to power a [[Planet/Legends|planet]], or even a new [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]].

==History==
The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] began researching this technology in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Restuss]] on [[Rori/Legends|Rori]]. During its developmental stages, the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebellion]] heard of this object and began amassing [[Troop/Legends|troops]] outside of the city. The Empire quickly evacuated the city of Restuss and prepared for battle. Largely because of the Star Core's importance to the Empire, [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] had arranged for additional elite forces to arrive at [[Rori/Legends|Rori]] via [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]] jump if the circumstances required it. During the climax of the [[Battle of Restuss]], something went terribly wrong with the Star Core. In its developmental stage, it exploded, destroying the once great city of Restuss.

